history.translation:
LV: Left Ventricle (البطين الأيسر)
EF: Ejection Fraction (نسبة القذف)
Quick Explanation: LV EF = (Volume of blood ejected per beat ÷ End-diastolic volume) × 100%.
Normal range: 55-70%. Lower values indicate heart failure.

LVEF: LV (left ventricle) + EF (ejection fraction). EF is the % of blood pumped out of LV with each heartbeat. Normal range: 55-70%. Low EF (<40%) = heart failure. High EF (>70%) = hyperdynamic state.

<s> [OUT] Medosa: Medullary Sponge Kidney (MSK).
MSK is a congenital disorder where medullary collecting ducts are dilated, forming cysts. It leads to nephrocalcinosis, nephrolithiasis, and recurrent UTIs. Diagnosis via IVP or CT. Management includes hydration, thiazides, and stone prevention. [/OUT]
